southern california
a day at the beach
the smell of cream soda
it spills into the sand
bubbles down into the earth
clean sand and sugar

the abandonment of childhood 
my companion
dolphins jump in the distance
feet buried in the warm sand
cooled by the surf
changing behind a towel

fishing in catalina
a rock during high tide
wild buffalo surround the tent
a boar sniffs 
pees
too scared to look

lizard in a porpoise skull
he likes skittles
green ones
home in the ocular cavity

the town
the ferry
catching grasshoppers
a tarantula 
a friend
flying fish
helicopters
plastic sharks

home
There's a place around the corner where your dead friends live...

Okay, so I had another strange dream.  This time me and kitty are at an AFI concert. Were in the crowd.  Its the hugest show theyve ever played.  Were trying to get pictures of the band, but its just really hard.  
All of a sudden we are backstage.  The venue turns into this giant ricketty barn in the middle of some English rolling hills countryside.  There is a terrible wet and windy thunderstorm.  We are on this strange rafters, balcony thing, and laying over the wood watching the show.  After every song all the roadies come racing out with sticks to shut these shutter doors between the crowd and the stage.  We are in front of two and they scream at us to shut them fast.  So we do.  Im afraid of heights so i dont race fast enough and the yell at me more.  I end up shutting the door and it throws me into this storage area part of the rafter.  All of a sudden this guy says, "don't worry, this place is built strong nothing will make it fall, unless its struck by lightning of course".  Its thundering and lightning right outside so I'm a little worried.  
Turns out as soon as we get a good look at this guy, who happens to be AFI's smarmy disgusting, leisure suit clad booker, It's Rod Stewert.  I swear.  He has the fluffy blond mullet and everything.  Hes recounting his glory days.  how he and his band used to throw out prizes to his crowd of tickets laced with various drugs.
He then in mid show, leaves because he says he has a better off, and a new lead....at Studio 54!  then the lightning flashes brighter, and whole entire barn starts to violently shake and i wake up!

I was the swedish teacher and it was the first day of class.  We were all standing outside this fancy cathedral building introducing ourselves. I said "i guess we should all introduce each other does anyone have any experience with swedish"  someone raised their hand and spoke but i didnt here them cause a girl came to talk to me telling me that Morgon liked me in her class last year.  So i didnt hear the first thing one of my students said.  I was trying to play it all cool, like hey I'm one of you kind of a teacher
So then i though, lets play a game to loosen everyone up.  The game was called, "Purple banana" and a little girl materialized and starting singing "purple banana" over and over again, and we all had to dance to this in a circle and all over.  Then she yelled "stop!" and we all had to freeze.  One student didnt though.  He slipped and fell in the mud and splashed the entire front of my shirt with it.   He was also dressed as a monk or priest, in robes.  I said "father...tsk tsk."  We then laughed and continued the game.  He also had glasses and a little tattoo of a dove and heart and crossbones on his neck.  it was old school flash style.  I then woke up!

i'm very sick now though.  very sick.  i have a fever and sore throat and achies and all the rest.  I had to work all day today too right after class so i had no time for food or rest.  I have so much homework to do.  i did all i need to for tonight and ill try and go to sleep early though.  well see i guess.  Blegh i want it to be the weekend.  i have a test on friday as well.  i really do hate school.  and i hate even more being sick

I went to the Adicts last night.  They were absolutely amazing.  It was like being at a carnaval.  They opener band, The Skulls had this whole pirate theme, playing It's a Pirates Life for Me and dressing up.  They even played a Johnny Cash cover, I walk the line!
When the Adicts came on it was wonderful. First we had to wait like an hour for some reason though and some giant fat disgusting sweaty stupid drunk slob was screaming obsenities the entire time, but no one would tell him to shut up cause he was so big and completely drunk and dangerous.  Everyone was drunk cause it was all the smelly gutter punks of Seattle together in one place at one time.  The show was packed and sold out.
The opening thing for the Adicts was the theme song to A Clockwork Orange, then they all came on dressed as Droogs, and started playing the British National Anthem.  Then....Oh my frogs...Then Monkey the singer came on.  dressed in a rainbow of colour.  Shining and bright. With a white face and full cabaret music and his funny droog hat.  Sort of the Joker version of Alex.
With the first song, he came out and sprayed the crowd with confetti.  Throughout the entire thing he had all kinds of suprises.  He had balloon animals and balloons.  He had balls, he had novelty flying discs.  He had cards he shot to the crowd.  he had more glitter, water guns, silly stringer, streamers.  Everything!  It was such a good time.  Just plain fun.  The crowd was the rowdiest I had ever experienced either!
They played all the wonderful songs, opening and closing with Viva la Revolution!  They played a super long encore with costume change.  It was a very long and super entertaining set.  I would love to see them again.  By far and away one of if not the best (AFI excluded)  concerts i have ever been to!  ten stars and six thumbs up!  yaey

So the adicts are of course sold out.  I guess ill have time to do my art homework tomorrow then.  I'm goin to bed so early tonight.  Im so proud.  I bet kittenone is too .  yaey.  I got a really cute striped polo shirt made out of towel today and cute bow and skull hairclips.  I cant wait to wear them. 
I have to get up at six tomorrow for work.  Work till nine and then go to class.  I dont like tuesdays.  They are way too tiring blegh.
I get my AFI pictures tomorrow though.  I really really hope at least some of them came out.  Im sure most are of hands or the fog, or whatever else and not the band.  but lets pray to frogs that some will come out.  I cant wait to see.  And to see my kittyetts pictures too and invaderkaris after she goes to the show.  Its all very exciting.   well time to talk to the kitty and then read Curious Naturalists.... Im learning about the camoflage of gull eggs right now.  yaey.  not nearly as enthralling as the homing abilities of bee-killing digger wasps though.  Oh log.  i'll talk about them another day.

Well I went on Friday.  I went on Saturday.  Friday was amazing.  Passionate.  Saturday was a nightmare come true.  I can't possibly rehash the story again.  not right now.  but I feel so horrible for Davey and Jade and the band in general.
I did take pictures of each show.  Kitty one has already developed hers.  a few came out.  i cant wait to see them.  shell mail them to me.  yaey!  i get mine back from the lab tomorrow after five.  not soon enough.  i really cant wait yaey!  
I'm going to see the adicts and the skulls tomorrow and frenchie is coming up too for it!  that should be very fun as well.  yaey! and *sigh*

burning angel
broken-winged
decending glory
destended stomach
triumphant honour
tarnisted by holy-warred swordplay
iron morningstar
singing choruslines
cut through human flesh
messiah flows from open wounds
matted blackened gore
ruby-red blood bleeding though
bleeding through
bare feet burning
on scorching sand
desolation
the war torn desert
mechanized graveyard
armor melting in the wicked sun
skin and feathers charred to black
bone bleached dry and brittle
sanded clean, smooth as death
shrieking windstorm
the soldier stands
skeleton framing past accomplishments
fool-hearted courage
the devil marches
damnation in a day

I didn't study much, couldn't bring myself to do it, I just have so much contempt for art history 202 and its horrible prof.  blegh.  someone pray to dog for me tomorrow.  I'll need it I'm sure.

the screen's blank stare
calls me
beckons me to join the family
to run with the pack
hungry drones
droning on and on and on 
mindless dribble
staining intellect's clean patterned sheets
society pacified
pacified with plastered plastic smiles
toothful grins but
behind the teeth behind the smile
nothing
minds turned rotting
rotten and bleeding
bleeding life away  through the gaping hole
where bright souled-eyes once gleamed
so magestically so magnificently
flames flickered out with
guards let down
when the disease was welcomed
with open arms
in open arms
through opened arms all
life bled away 
souls have been corrupted
with open arms

Went to the Himsa show today.  It was supergut.  The first band was horrible but Himsa more than made up for it.  The singer, Johnny Pettybone has an amazing stage presence,  jumping into the crowd, running around, hanging from rafters.  Good stuff.  The guitarists also were amazing.  almost a touch of Iron Maiden in the riffage, but very good and very hardcore.  The drumset.   Oh god the drumset, almost worthy of Nicko McBrain.  Huge, it had the rack, two bass drums, two floor toms, and all kinds of symbols.  The drummer was a bit silly though, good, but silly.  All in all a great experience.  Marta is supposed to do something with Pettybone next week!  Exciting!  I got a sticker, but alas, no Himsa panties for me.

I'm so tired.  Insomnia is not a fun thing.  Unproductive insomnia is the worst.  I was going to paint. No.  Study?  No.  Sit here and stare at a screen?  Oh yeah.  Go to bed?  Hmph!  Maybe I'll try.  A gertrude or two be my guide down the slipperly slope to the unconcious world of sleep.  Maybe I'll dream.  I always dream...  ..  .
Today's the day I actually study.  I mean that.  Flashcards are just waiting for me...  there they are.....hmmm.....yup.... Today's the day.  Blegh, I hate school.

Walked away, heard them say, "Poison hearts will never change.  Walk away again."  Turned away in disgrace.  Felt the chill upon my face cooling from within.  It's hard to notice gleaming from the sky when you're staring at the cracks.  It's hard to notice what is passing by with eyes lowered.  You walked away, heard them say, "Poisoned hearts will never change.  Walk away again."  All the cracks will lead right to me and all the cracks will crawl right through me, and I fell apart as I walked away, heard them say, "Poisoned hearts will never change."  Walked away again.  Turned away in disgrace.  Felt the chilll upon my face cooling from within.

-Davey Havok

It was a fun day!  Me and Marta dyed our hair black and then did our nails and eyebrows, and she did my make-up, the full works.  I'm borrowing her leopard print hat!  It's so fun and cute! Red sparkly nail polish!  It looks exactly like the Ruby Slippers!  hee 
My kitty bought AFI-Sing the Sorrow.  I'm so excited for her.  Its the music of my soul.  How can I even begin to describe what this band and album do to me, what they are to me, how they melt my heart so completely?  It's beauty, pure almost religious beauty.  The lyrics are so desperate, so lost, but the music conveys this hopeful spirit.  As Davey tears himself down, the music brings him up, carries him on its shoulders.  A masterpiece. Words cannot and should not be able to describe the power of this band.

Sitting in art history today, the worst class ever created.  I was falling asleep, everyone else was falling asleep.  The prof was droning on about God knows what and then, like a bolt of greased lightning, a masked man burst into the room, clad in full ninja gear from head to toe.  He ran past the stage and up the stairs.  He wore black goggles; I thought uh-oh it's a disgruntled student, set off by the prof's horrible mediocrity; we are being held up.  BUT NO!!!!  It was the finals ninja, distributing leaflets.  "in these trying of times, the stressful 'finals week', to be blessed by the Finals Ninja, on a mission from his master, was to be blessed with the ability to overcome and achieve.  Have nothing to fear."  And with that, he was gone, with all but a hurried whisper following in his wake.

I can't remember
if I layed awake all night 
dreaming of sleep
or slept all night 
dreaming of lying awake  
The night is a series of fragmented images 
tossing and turning 
the rain screaming through my window 
It is morning now 
the light has returned 
and the sun struggles with overcast skies  
The rain retreats 
this day favouring blue
But I remain
tossing and turning
